President Donald Trump delivered remarks at the White House to celebrate Hanukkah. He expressed his condolences for the recent passing of President George H.W. Bush and praised his legacy. Trump also acknowledged the tragic shooting at the Tree of Life synagogue in Pittsburgh and reaffirmed the commitment to combat anti-Semitism. He honored Holocaust survivors in attendance and emphasized the importance of never forgetting history. The President highlighted the strong relationship between the United States and Israel, including the relocation of the American embassy to Jerusalem. He concluded by lighting the menorah and wishing everyone a happy Hanukkah. Vice President Mike Pence also spoke, expressing his support for Israel and extending Hanukkah wishes.